# LeetCode 3314 — Construct the Minimum Bitwise Array I (C++)

This problem is about constructing an array `ans` using bitwise operators, specifically by finding values that satisfy a condition with OR and `+1`.

## Key Takeaways
- Practiced bitwise shifting in C++: `<<` and `>>`
- Used a “sliding mask” approach (a moving bit probe) to scan binary patterns
- Learned how to detect the first `0` bit after a run of trailing `1`s

## Core Idea (Mask Scan)
For each `p = nums[i]`:
- Start with `mask = 1` (binary `...0001`)
- While `(p & mask) != 0`, shift the mask left (`mask <<= 1`) to move through trailing `1`s
- When the loop stops, we found the first `0` bit after the trailing `1`s
- Step back one bit using `mask >> 1` to get the value to subtract
- Compute `res = p - (mask >> 1)` and append it to `ans`

Special case:
- If `nums[i] == 2`, the answer is `-1` (it won’t work for that value in this problem’s setup)

## C++ Solution

```cpp
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> minBitwiseArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<int> ans;

        for (size_t i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i) {
            if (nums[i] == 2) { // special case
                ans.push_back(-1);
            } else {
                int p = nums[i];

                // mask is our "sliding window" bit probe
                int mask = 1;

                // Move left while the current bit in p is 1
                while ((p & mask) != 0) {
                    mask <<= 1;
                }

                // mask is now at the first 0 bit after trailing 1s,
                // so move back one step
                int sub = mask >> 1;

                int res = p - sub;
                ans.push_back(res);
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
